Turkcell Agrees to Buy Global Iletisim From Yildiz Holding

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-08-13T11:00:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-13/turkcell-agrees-to-buy-global-iletisim-from-yildiz-holding.html
Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS,
 Turkey ’s biggest mobile operator, agreed to buy  Global Iletisim
AS , a telecommunications data operator, from Yildiz Holding AS,
it said.  Global Iletisim was valued at 17.5 million liras ($10
million), Turkcell said in an e-mailed statement today. The
actual purchase price will be determined by evaluating Global’s
debts, loans and cash position at the close of the transaction,
it said.  Global Iletisim, which also offers cloud computing services
to its corporate clients, has three data centers in Ankara and
Istanbul which will be integrated with Turkcell Superonline AS,
Turkcell’s fiber-optic and Internet services provider unit, the
company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 